<TITLE> Nafees makes way for Nazimuddin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 12 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh opener Shahriar Nafees has pull out of the upcoming Australia tour on Tuesday over study priorities, making way for Nazimuddin. "Shahriar Nafees has opted out of the tour of Australia due to the sudden announcement of his university exam schedule and Nafees made the request in a letter to the Board Tuesday," Bangladesh Cricket Board said in a press statement. It said the BCB selection committee decided to replace Nafees with Nazimuddin, one of the five reserve players. The BCB on Sunday announced a 15-member squad for the tour entailing three one-day internationals and five practice matches, scheduled for Aug 15- September 7. "In the past I had sat exam under special arrangements because of to my national duties and I have already lost one and a half years," Nafees said. "This time, I want to sit the exams on the university's announced schedules." Nafees said the final exams would get underway in September after the completion of the in-course exams this month. Bangladesh leave for Darwin on Aug 14 and will play five one-day practice matches there before the ODI series against the world champions. They will play four practice matches against Australian Institute of Sports on Aug 18, 20, 23 and 25 and one against Territory Chief Minister's XI, scheduled for Aug 27. Bangladesh will take on Ricky Ponting's men in the ODI series opener on Aug 30 while the second and third matches are scheduled for Sept 3 and 6 respectively. b
